Pacific Map, summer 1941

Eric Rauchway

6/10/2022

Map data draws principally from Natural Earth datasets, at various resolutions. Ive drawn for reference on other sources, including Andr Ouredniks historical basemaps repository; for occupied China, I relied on Greg Huff, World War II and Southeast Asia. For colors I drew mainly from CARTOcolors. When all else has failed Ive looked up latitudes and longitudes in Wikipedia. Made with R, including ggplot and sf, as well as some use of QGIS. With gratitude especially to Kieran Healy.
